                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12760934" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 30 Sep 2009 15:45:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Let&apos;s be a little more rigorous here.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should require that min &amp;lt;= max.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;min == max == 0 should disable compaction.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;otherwise, min should be &amp;gt;= 2.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12762686" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 6 Oct 2009 16:56:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;maxthreshold default should be a constant in CompactionManager (that CM also defaults to of course)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;currently max=0 disables compaction sort of by accident (from the sublist call in CFS.doCompaction), which generates a Warning log message.  we should add a special case to doCompaction that doesn&apos;t call doFileCompaction at all in that case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12763277" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 7 Oct 2009 21:35:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;imo the info line you added should be debug level for consistency.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;other than that +1, go ahead and commit w/o an extra patch cycle&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12763472" author="hudson" created="Thu, 8 Oct 2009 12:35:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra #221 (See &lt;a href=&quot;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/221/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/221/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    Added the ability to set maxthreshold to zero in nodeprobe, and added a special case to CF.doCompaction to not run compaction when its disabled. patch by goffinet; reviewed by jbellis for &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
